                            <comment id="431967" author="adilger" created="Mon, 21 Oct 2024 01:34:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This looks like it is just variability in the test times due to running in a VM, since the delay from reading the mirror is only a few seconds.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It probably makes sense to have some small margin of error (5s?) to prevent the test from failing if the read time is not very long.  This should only be considered an error if the read RPC is timing out (e.g. tens or hundreds of seconds).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
